84 /** test the interface of CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData for null pointer and invalid parameters */
85 void testCAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalDataInterfaceNullPointer(void) {
86  uint64_t message = 0;
87  uint64_t bitStart = 0;
88  uint8_t bitLength = 0;
89  uint64_t canSignal = 0;
90  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
91 
92  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness));
93 
94  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(NULL_PTR, 1u, 1u, canSignal, endianness));
95 
96  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 64u, 0u, canSignal, endianness));
97  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 1u, 65u, canSignal, endianness));
98  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 65u, 64u, canSignal, endianness));
99  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 10u, 64u, canSignal, endianness));
100 
101  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 1u, 1u, canSignal, CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN));
102  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 1u, 1u, canSignal, CAN_BIG_ENDIAN));
103  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, 1u, 1u, canSignal, INT8_MAX));
104 }
105 
106 /** test CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData with various signals */
107 void testCAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData64BitMessage(void) {
108  uint64_t message = 0;
109  uint64_t bitStart = 0;
110  uint8_t bitLength = 63;
111  uint64_t canSignal = UINT64_MAX >> 1u;
112  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
113 
114  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness);
115 
116  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL_UINT64(canSignal, message);
117 
118  message = 0;
119  bitStart = 0;
120  bitLength = 64;
121  canSignal = UINT64_MAX;
122  endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
123 
124  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness);
125 
126  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL_UINT64(canSignal, message);
127 
128  message = 0;
129  bitStart = 0;
130  bitLength = 1;
131  canSignal = 0x1u;
132  endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
133 
134  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness);
135 
136  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL_UINT64(canSignal, message);
137 
138  message = 0;
139  bitStart = 0;
140  bitLength = 3;
141  canSignal = 0x7u;
142  endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
143 
144  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness);
145 
146  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL_UINT64(canSignal, message);
147 
148  message = 0;
149  bitStart = 0;
150  bitLength = 3;
151  canSignal = UINT64_MAX;
152  endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
153 
154  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness);
155  /* This behavior is a by-product of implementation and you should not necessarily rely on it */
156  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL_UINT64(0x7u, message);
157 
158  message = 0;
159  bitStart = 5;
160  bitLength = 2;
161  canSignal = 0x3u;
162  endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
163 
164  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(&message, bitStart, bitLength, canSignal, endianness);
165 
166  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL_UINT64(0x60u, message);
167 }

169 /** test the interface of CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData for null pointer and invalid parameters */
170 void testCAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageDataInterfaceNullPointer(void) {
171  uint64_t message = 0;
172  uint64_t bitStart = 0;
173  uint8_t bitLength = 0;
174  uint64_t pCanSignal = 0;
175  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness = CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
176 
177  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, bitStart, bitLength, &pCanSignal, endianness));
178 
179  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 1u, 1u, NULL_PTR, endianness));
180 
181  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 64u, 0u, &pCanSignal, endianness));
182  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 1u, 65u, &pCanSignal, endianness));
183  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 65u, 64u, &pCanSignal, endianness));
184  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 10u, 64u, &pCanSignal, endianness));
185 
186  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 1u, 1u, &pCanSignal, CAN_LITTLE_ENDIAN));
187  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(CAN_RxGetSignalDataFromMessageData(message, 1u, 1u, &pCanSignal, CAN_BIG_ENDIAN));

254 void testCAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(void) {
255  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(false));
256  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(1u, CAN_ConvertBooleanToInteger(true));
257 }
